{
  "stem": "8786.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "By coming home we says that probably they had found the Hungarians, that they ask us to burn as many buildings as-- as we can.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They probably put on some gasoline [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were marching and burning, burning and marching, and-- and this was even on the holiday of Yom Kippur we were doing it, coming back from Osmoloda, back toward Hungary.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This was in the Carpathian area which is called Ruthenia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Today it's Ruthenia, belongs today to Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was the time when we did hear-- we were in a town, it's called Huszt, probably.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "October 15th we heard on the big news that the Hungarian regent, Admiral Nicholas Horthy, gave a notice on the radio that he is looking [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for peace.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He doesn't want to continue the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Naturally, he was foolish enough to let the Germans know what he wants to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the Germans just picked him up and took him away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And this big holiday what we expected that the next day the whole thing will be over fizzled out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Unfortunately, it didn't happen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But instead of Horthy, the Germans took over.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Veesenmayer was the German consulate-- consul general.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Actually he was the-- Hitler's main representative in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And he was already dictating what the Hungarian government should do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They appointed this biggest dog what Hungary had was Szalasi, this most brutal animal who was-- who took over the government.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The most brutal way he was, he and his [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] group, which was called the-- they called it [NON-ENGLISH], but they have a word for it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They had the arrow, the arrow-- they had the--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Arrow Cross.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were the most sadistic youngsters you can imagine.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
